 machines from the terminal with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI."}],"title":"Using the spook Command-Line Interface"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/MLWorkloads":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/mlworkloads","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run ML training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines."}],"title":"Machine Learning Workloads"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/KubernetesGuide":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/kubernetesguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines as Kubernetes resources using the MacOSVM custom resource definition."}],"title":"Kubernetes Integration"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/RemoteDesktop":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/remotedesktop","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to Spooktacular VMs via VNC for remote development, QA testing, and design review."}],"title":"Remote Desktop Access"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GitHubActionsGuide":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/githubactionsguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run self-hosted macOS GitHub Actions runners in Spooktacular VMs with ephemeral isolation and automatic scaling."}],"title":"Configuring GitHub Actions Runners"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/BlueBubblesGuide":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/bluebubblesguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Set up a BlueBubbles iMessage server in a macOS VM — a dramatically simpler alternative to VMware on Windows."}],"title":"Running BlueBubbles iMessage Server"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/jenkinsguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS CI\/CD."}],"title":"Configuring Jenkins Nodes"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GettingStarted":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release."}],"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","type":"topic","kind":"article"}}}